         Thank you for posting this guide.</P><P>I would like to add some extra info and correct some minor errors (heres hoping im right with the corrections ;) )</P><P>Firstly the minor corrections which I'm sure most will be aware of... but you never know :)</P><P>The Eye of Inorruuk drops in Hate.... and the Slime Blood of Cazic Thule drops in Fear.</P><P>Secondly some extra info on the Grand Herbalist Mah'Ka.</P><P>My group and I reached him yesterday the group consisted of the following (1 Tank 56th 1 Cleric 57th 1 Enchanter 57th 1 Monk 56th 1 Druid 57th and me the Necro 54th).  Getting to him was easy enough in that we took our time no undue rushing (we did have one wipeout when our monk logged for tea and our tank pulled just as a named mob popped on her - np, summoned rezzed and headed back down to rejoin monk who was back from tea :) ).</P><P>The loc of the herbalist is p50 (reading east to west) and p150 (reading north to south) - hopefully that is in the correct order but for the life of me I cant remember which number comes up first on /loc.  Also the loc is general in nature as I'm a necro and sulked around the back of the group and our valient monk did the pulling :) - however that should be enough to highlight the house he is found in on any good Chardok map (there are a few to be found on eqmaps.com).</P><P>Anyways I was lucky enough that he dropped herb first time ( as missus was aggroing on me worse than the good lady Vox :) and I had to log very shortly after that ).</P><P>Finally just to thank my group again for their help.</P><P>Cheers</P><P><BR>Myrkul Undeadmaster<BR>54th Heretic<BR>Dragons of Saint George<BR>Quellious<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
